HEADWORD: Pouncet box
<hw>Poun"cet box`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>poncette</ets>,
fr. <ets>ponce</ets> pounce. See <er>Pounce</er> a powder.]</ety> <def>A
box with a perforated lid, for sprinkling pounce, or for holding
perfumes.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pouncing</ent>⟦br⟧
